  <div xmlns:v="http://rdf.data-vocabulary.org/#" typeof="v:Review">
    <div class="main review-item" id="1501742">
        

  <header class="main-hd">
    <h3 class="title">
      <a href="https://book.douban.com/review/1501742/" class="title-link">关于摇滚乐可能进行的改变</a>
      <div class="toggle_review right">        <a href="javascript:;" id="toggle-1501742"class="indicator unfold j" title="展开全文">        </a>
      </div>
    </h3>
    

<div class="header-more">
    <a class="author-avatar" href="https://www.douban.com/people/pushusep/"><img width="48" height="48" src="https://img3.doubanio.com/icon/u1260502-582.jpg"></a>
    <a href="https://www.douban.com/people/pushusep/" class="author">
      <span property="v:reviewer">朴九月 CL</span>
    </a>    <span property="v:rating" class="allstar40 main-title-rating" title="推荐"></span>
  <span property="v:dtreviewed" content="2008-09-20"
      class="main-meta">2008-09-20 15:18:19</span>
</div>

  </header>

        <div class="main-bd">
          <div id="review_1501742_short" class="review-short">
            <div class="short-content">
                  （Hit轻音乐2008年8月专稿，勿转。）  “摇滚乐”与“政治”，当台湾人张铁志在这样一种氛围环境下出版以此二者为主题的文化评论书籍时，就应该预料到它所有可能引发的争议。此二者本身在独立时便具备的暧昧含义，就足够让张铁志的问句“摇滚乐可能改变世界吗？”成为永远没有...

                    <a class="pl" href="https://book.douban.com/review/1501742/#comments">(11回应)</a>
                  <div class="more-info pl clearfix">
                    <span class="left">5有用 / 0没用</span>
                  </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div id="review_1501742_full" class="hidden">
            <div id="review_1501742_full_content" class="full-content"></div>
          </div>
        </div>
    </div>
  </div>





